      "content": "This is a complex tension between religious freedom and governmental authority. Proponents of religious exemptions argue that the First Amendment protects sincerely held beliefs from government compulsion. Conversely, those prioritizing secularism argue that granting exemptions weakens the state's ability to enforce universal laws and principles. A healthy democracy requires balancing these competing rights, often through narrowly tailored legal frameworks rather than absolute adherence to one side.",
